From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0050/N] mlib_image_types.h: handle CHERI sizeof(void*)=16 in reserved[]

`mlib_image` (libmlib_image / Java 2D) computes a reserved padding
array sized to round the struct to one 64-byte cache line:

  mlib_s32    reserved[7 - 2*sizeof(void*)/4];

On 64-bit Linux: 7 - 2*8/4 = 7 - 4 = 3 elements. On CHERI purecap
where sizeof(void*) = 16 (capability), the formula gives 7 - 8 = -1,
which clang treats as a huge unsigned -- "array is too large
(18446744073709551615 elements)".

The cache-line alignment is an optimization, not a correctness
requirement. Under purecap drop the padding to one element.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0050)

--- a/src/java.desktop/share/native/libmlib_image/mlib_image_types.h
+++ b/src/java.desktop/share/native/libmlib_image/mlib_image_types.h
@@ -124,7 +124,13 @@ typedef struct {
   mlib_s32    bitoffset;   /* the offset in bits from the beginning    */
                            /* of the data buffer to the first pixel    */
   mlib_format format;      /* pixels format                            */
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  /* CHERI purecap pointers are 16 bytes; the original formula yields negative
+     reserved size. Drop cache-line padding to one element. */
+  mlib_s32    reserved[1];
+#else
   mlib_s32    reserved[7 - 2*sizeof(void*)/4];
+#endif
                            /* Reserved for future use. Also makes      */
                            /* size of this structure = 64 bytes, which */
                            /* is the size of the cache line.           */
